// What command stat myfile.txt do?
-- using man stat,
   we can discover that it will show file statistics for my file.txt

// df -h/ do?
-- again using man df
shows disk utilization of root file system in human readable way

// What command use to search for file directory hierarchy
-- using apropos command

// which option would use with ls command to o/p a comma separated list of files and directories.
-- using (man ls) & then (ls -m)

// all command are below mentioned...
@Subhomoy21 ➜ /workspaces/LearningLinux (main) $ man stat
@Subhomoy21 ➜ /workspaces/LearningLinux (main) $ man df
@Subhomoy21 ➜ /workspaces/LearningLinux (main) $ apropos "search for files"
find (1)             - search for files in a directory hierarchy
@Subhomoy21 ➜ /workspaces/LearningLinux (main) $ man ls
@Subhomoy21 ➜ /workspaces/LearningLinux (main) $ ls -m
